# Documentation Authoring

Follow `docs/policy/documentation-policy.md` for the full policy. Key rules summarized here.

## Content Type Selection

Every page belongs to exactly one of five types. Choose based on user intent:

| Type | Directory | Question it answers |
|---|---|---|
| Quickstart | `getting-started/quick-start.mdx` | "How do I get this working in 5 minutes?" |
| Tutorial | `getting-started/*.mdx` | "How do I learn this properly?" |
| How-to guide | `guides/*.mdx` | "How do I accomplish this specific task?" |
| Explanation | `concepts/*.mdx` | "Why does this work this way?" |
| Reference | `api/*.mdx` | "What are the exact types and signatures?" |

Follow the structural template for the chosen type (see policy Section 3).

## Frontmatter (Required)

```yaml
---
title: Descriptive Title  # NOT generic "Overview"
description: What this page covers in under 160 characters
icon: lucide:icon-name  # optional
---
```

## Code Examples

- TypeScript only.
- Include ALL imports with full package paths (`@taucad/kernels`, `@taucad/kernels/kernels`).
- Complete, runnable snippets -- never fragments.
- Annotate expected output.

## Page Self-Containment

Every page must make sense in isolation (EPPO principle). Never assume prior reading. Link prerequisites. Include all imports in code blocks.

## AI Discoverability

- Keep pages under 2000 words.
- Use headings every 200-400 words.
- Fenced code blocks with language tags.
- `description` frontmatter is mandatory (populates `/llms.txt`).

## Cross-Linking

Every page links to at least one page of a different content type in its Related/Next Steps section.

## API Reference

Reference pages use `<auto-type-table>` from `fumadocs-typescript`. Props files in `api/props/` re-export only public API types. No internal type leakage.
